definitions.definition: To make repeated changes to a file or data which individually may be reversible, yet which ultimately result in an unintentional irreversible destruction of large portions of the original data.
To harm , to damage ; to destroy .

main_definition: ( computing , informal ) To make repeated changes to a file or data which individually may be reversible, yet which ultimately result in an unintentional irreversible destruction of large portions of the original data.
secondary_definitions: ( by extension , informal ) To harm , to damage ; to destroy .
